T1  - A continuous time approach to the pricing of bonds
AU  - Brennan, Michael J.
AU  - Schwartz, Eduardo S.
JO  - Journal of Banking & Finance
VL  - 3
IS  - 2
SP  - 133
EP  - 155
PY  - 1979
DA  - 1979/07/01/
SN  - 0378-4266
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0378-4266(79)90011-6
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0378426679900116
AB  - This paper develops an arbitrage model of the term structure of interest rates based on the assumptions that the whole term structure at any point in time may be expressed as a function of the yields on the longest and shortest maturity default free instruments and that these two yields follow a Gauss-Wiener process. Arbitrage arguments are used to derive a partial differential equation which must be satisfied by the values of all default free bonds. The joint stochastic process for the two yields is estimated using Canadian data and the model is used to price a sample of Government of Canada bonds.
ER  - 

